      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Please note that the <code>volatile</code> keyword used in this way only applies to Java. In C or C++, the <code>volatile</code> keyword does not guarantee atomicity, but instead tries to guarantee that a change made in one thread is always visible in another—partial reads and writes are still possible."
