      "comment_id" : 118966331,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "In C#/.NET, <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2076461/how-does-c-sharp-guarantee-the-atomicity-of-read-write-operations\">several types are guaranteed always atomic</a>, including object references. For other types, you should use locking or the <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.threading.interlocked?view=net-5.0\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Interlocked class</a>."
    } ],
