      "creation_date" : 1670390974,
      "post_id" : 24410004,
      "comment_id" : 131863289,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "yeah, that&#39;s fair.  I guess my point is that people may read &quot;instantaneous&quot; and by analogy with normal expectations of linear time, make the jump to assuming linearizability - where if one operation happens before another, you see the effects in that order as well.  Which is not a guarantee individual atomic operations offer when combined."
